{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01ANc5ubpKd9GLmTbbutLM9Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"WP1 + WP2 for Round 4 is complete. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n---\n\n## WP1 (Ideation) — Complete\n\n**`round4/research.md`** contains 3 novel ideas, each addressing the binding constraints from R3:\n\n### Idea 1: Multi-Objective Constrained CMA-ES with ITL Penalty\n- **Attacks:** BC-NEW-1 (E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff) directly\n- **Approach:** Same CMA-ES pipeline as R3, but with penalty-augmented dual-objective (`0.5*E2E + 0.5*ITL + penalty`), parameter bounds (OTPT ≤ 500μs), and integrated TTFT corrections\n- **Expected:** E2E < 12%, ITL < 20%\n\n### Idea 2: Data-Driven Step Cycle Time Regression\n- **Attacks:** BC-NEW-2 (step cycle under-prediction) — the root cause of the E2E ↔ ITL tradeoff\n- **Approach:** Train regression on *actual inter-token intervals* (ITI) from lifecycle data instead of `step.duration_us`, eliminating the overhead floor heuristic entirely\n- **Expected:** E2E < 25%, ITL < 20%, without any CMA-ES\n- **Literature:** FairBatching's `a + b*new_tokens + c*kv_sum` (±1.3%), Vidur's operator-level RF models (<5% P95)\n\n### Idea 3: Hybrid — Principled Base + Constrained CMA-ES Residual\n- **Attacks:** All binding constraints by combining Ideas 1 and 2\n- **Approach:** Stage 1 = cycle-time regression (correct base), Stage 2 = tightly bounded CMA-ES (±20% of base values, dual objective)\n- **Expected:** E2E < 10%, ITL < 15% — the full research target\n\nAll three ideas include vLLM args sensitivity analysis, LOMO plans, and LOWO plans per BC-1-7.\n\n## WP2 (Scaffolding) — Complete\n\nThree idea directories created under `round4/`:\n- `idea-1-constrained-cmaes/HYPOTHESIS.md` — 4 sub-hypotheses (H1: constrained CMA-ES, H2: Pareto sweep, H3: LOMO, H4: LOWO)\n- `idea-2-cycle-time-regression/HYPOTHESIS.md` — 4 sub-hypotheses (H1: cycle-time extraction, H2: FairBatching regression + BLIS E2E, H3: LOMO, H4: LOWO)\n- `idea-3-hybrid-calibration/HYPOTHESIS.md` — 4 sub-hypotheses (H1: Stage 1 base, H2: Stage 2 CMA-ES residual, H3: LOMO, H4: LOWO)\n\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**The diagnostic structure of Round 4:**\n- Ideas form a controlled experiment: Idea 1 tests optimization improvements alone, Idea 2 tests base model improvements alone, Idea 3 combines both. This decomposition lets us attribute gains precisely.\n- The novel element is Idea 2's target variable change: modeling ITI (inter-token interval, actual cycle time) instead of `step.duration_us` (GPU-only time). This addresses the root cause behind both major binding constraints.\n- Each idea has its own short-circuit criteria to prevent wasted computation if early hypotheses fail.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\n**Marker file:** `.phase1_done` created — the orchestrator can proceed to WP3 phases."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fa10f5df-2c8f-4bb1-b1a9-38b8d7356b7f","uuid":"ba9dde1d-5644-4025-aed2-9a3a2e24971a"}
